node.text: @kiacooks credits her mom and grandma for instilling in her a love of good food and cooking, and in today’s episode of Secret Family Recipe, Kia makes one of her grandma’s signature dishes, Chicken & Stuff, with an assist from her mom. Tap the link in our bio for Kia’s family recipe. #thekitchn

node.text: If you’ve ever tried to spread cold, straight-out-of-the-fridge butter on toast using a mere butter knife, you now how fruitless it can be. Instead of beautifully, evenly buttered toast, you get splotchy, torn bread with some butter here and clumps of butter there. Luckily, there’ are gadgets for that! Ones that promise to spread cold butter just *like that* — no tears, no problems, no buttery dreams dashed. 🧈 Of course, @riddley_s had to know if they worked, so she tried 5 — and the winner is only $5. Tap the link in our bio for all the details. (Image: @sarahecrowley) #thekitchn

node.text: If you’ve spent even just 2 minutes on this app recently, you’ve likely seen no fewer than 3,359 different grazing tables and cheese boards in your feed. Yes, they are trendy with a capital T, but how do you actually set one up? What food should you buy? Where should you put your first pile? And the second? And, good gosh, how do you even know if you’ll have enough food? Take a deep breath. We’re here to help. Tap the link in our bio for our printable templates, which can turn anyone into a charcuterie champ! (Video: @joe.lingeman, Styling: @jesseszewczyk) #thekitchn
